cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper discusses deep learning techniques in computer vision, specifically in semantic segmentation, and how they are vulnerable to adversarial attacks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a solution using denoise autoencoder, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The topic of adversarial attacks also relates to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the use of denoise autoencoder involves neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
